st - simple terminal
--------------------
st is a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.

Notes
-----
This is a fork of st that includes useful patches and tweaks.

The original repo can be found here: https://st.suckless.org/

Patches
-------
st-bold-is-not-bright-20190127-3be4cf1.diff
st-clickurl-0.8.5.diff
st-externalpipe-0.8.5.diff
st-externalpipe-eternal-0.8.3.diff
st-gruber-darker-0.9.2.diff
st-hidecursor-0.8.3.diff
st-scrollback-0.8.5.diff

Additionally, I borrowed scripts for interacting with the screen output
from Luke Smith's version of st: https://github.com/LukeSmithxyz/st

Added shortcuts
---------------
Alt + p   Scroll up
Alt + n   Scroll down
Alt + l   Open URL in browser
Alt + y   Copy URL
Alt + t   Copy output


Requirements
------------
In order to build st you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (st is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install st (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running st
----------
If you did not install st with make clean install, you must compile
the st terminfo entry with the following command:

    tic -sx st.info

See the man page for additional details.

